1. Install your liked OS. I prefer Debian Linux
2. In command lone use next command: python3 --version 
    if all correct then next step. Else install python3
3. Install git in your system. Also apt install git
4. Create folder workhistory. Also mkdir /home/user_name/workhistory
5. cd /home/user_name/workhistory
6. git clone https://github.com/saibogo/work_history.git
7. apt install pip
8. apt install python3-psycopg2
9. apt install python3-tk
10. apt install python3-flask
11. apt install python3-psutil
12. pip3 install fpdf
13. apt install python3-pyqt5
14. apt install postgresql
15. su  (And insert your superuser password)
16. su - postgres
17. psql -Upostgres
18. =# CREATE USER saibogo WITH PASSWORD 'myPassword';
19. =# CREATE DATABASE workhistory;
20. =# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE "workhistory" to saibogo;
21. =# \c workhistory
22. workhistory=# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO "saibogo";
23. exit to normal terminal
24. psql workhistory < /path/to/your/dump.db
25. python3 /path/to/main.py --help
Well Done!
26. edit config.py in your favorite editor (patches and ip)
27. python3 /path/to/main.py
28. start web-server
29. in your browser go to to http://your_ip:5000
Well Done!
